1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nf6 3. Nxe5 d6 4. Nf3 Nxe4 5. Nc3 Nxc3 6. dxc3 Be7 7. Be3 {This is White's most popular continuation. Before studying the big main line with 7.Be3 0-0 8.Qd2 in Lesson 15, we are taking a look at White's lesser options on move eight.} O-O 8. Bd3 {White prepares Qe2, followed by castling queenside. However, the queen will not be comfortable on e2 after a possible .. .Re8.} (8. Bc4 {is not very logical since Black can play} c6 {- now ...d5 is coming with tempo.} 9. O-O (9. Qd2 d5 10. Bd3 Nd7 11. O-O-O Nc5 $11) 9... Bg4 10. h3 Bh5 $11) (8. h4 {An aggressive try - White prepares a direct attack with Bd3, Ng5, etc.} Nd7 9. Bd3 (9. Ng5 $6 {is premature since it allows} Ne5 $15) (9. Qd3 {Putting the queen on d3 has no advantages over developing it to the more natural d2-square.} Nf6 10. O-O-O Bg4 11. Be2 Re8 $132) 9... Nc5 (9... Nf6) (9... Re8) 10. Ng5 h6 {With correct play, Black can defend and achieve a good game.} 11. Qe2 (11. Qd2 Nxd3+ (11... d5 $5) 12. Qxd3 g6 {transposes.}) (11. Bh7+ Kh8 12. Bd3 d5 $132 {Black could also repeat moves with 12...Kg8, but he does not need to.}) 11... Nxd3+ (11... d5 $5) 12. Qxd3 g6 {Black is solid enough on the kingside - ...Bf5 is coming with tempo.} 13. Ne4 (13. Nf3 h5 14. O-O-O Re8 $11) 13... Bf5 $5 {This is one of several good options for Black. Also playable are:} (13... d5 14. Ng3 h5) (13... Re8) 14. Bxh6 Re8 15. O-O-O Bf8 16. Bxf8 Bxe4 17. Qd4 Kxf8 18. Rde1 f5 {Black is up a piece; White's compensation is only good enough for a draw.} 19. f3 (19. Qh8+ Kf7 20. Qh7+ Kf8 $11) 19... Bc6 20. Qh8+ Kf7 21. Qh7+ Kf8 $11) (8. Qd3 Nd7 9. O-O-O Nc5 (9... c6 {should also be good.}) 10. Qc4 b6 11. Qf4 Bb7 12. h4 Qd7 $132) 8... Re8 ({Black has other decent options:} 8... Nd7) (8... c6) 9. Qe2 {As we already mentioned, this is an independent try.} (9. Qd2 Nd7 10. O-O-O Nf6 {transposes to the next lesson.}) (9. h4 Nd7 10. Qd2 Nf6 11. O-O-O {also transposes to the next lesson.}) 9... Nd7 10. O-O-O Nf6 (10... Bf8 {is also fine.}) 11. h3 (11. Rhe1 Bf8) 11... Bd7 12. Rhe1 (12. g4 $6 Bf8) 12... Bf8 $132 {[%csl Re2] Black has a good game - the queen is not well-placed on e2.} *

